{{Quote|The Empire won't stop until it reaches the edge of the galaxy, is that it?''"<br />"''Why stop there?|[[Has Obitt]] and [[Wilhuff Tarkin]], the latter of which showing interest in the potential for extragalactic expansion|<ref name="Catalyst">''[[Catalyst: A Rogue One Novel]]''</ref>}}
'''Extragalactic''' was a term for anything situated, occurring, or originating outside the [[Galactic Rim|boundaries]] of [[the galaxy]]. The [[Wild Space]]<ref name="EURWS">{{EncyclopediaCite|Exegol, the Unknown Regions and Wild Space}}</ref> [[planet]] [[Kamino]] and the rest of [[Kamino system|its]] [[star system]] were sometimes classed as extragalactic locations.<ref name="SWCL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> The planet [[Peridea]] was located in another galaxy, the [[far galaxy]].<ref name="Part Six: Far, Far Away">{{Ahsoka|Part Six: Far, Far Away}}</ref>

